		<profileDesc>
			<abstract>
				<p>We describe pulse-stream firing integrated circuits that implement asynchronous analog neural networks. Synaptic weights are stored dynamically, and weighting uses time-division of the neural pulses from a signalling neuron to a receiving neuron. MOS transistors in their &quot;ON&quot; state act as variable resistors to control a capacitive discharge, and time-division is thus achieved by a small synapse circuit cell. The VLSI chip set design uses 2.5J.1.m CMOS technology.</p>
			</abstract>
